o offers a message of hope. Namely, it is only once we comprehend the magnitude of the threat to our spatial experience and our own complicity in sustaining this system that we can begin to resist the totalizing forces at work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical theory. 0aSpacexPhilosophy. 0aSpacexPolitical aspects. 0aTotalitarianismxSocial aspects. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Critical Theory. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2019z978311149143140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438472935423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438472935/original  a978-3-11-149143-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles